track_notes: In March 2021 the last mile included compacted snow, ice, and deep snow at final ridge line to summit. Microspikes and poles essential.
track_title: Track from Tahquitz Summit to Humber Park Trailhead

track_notes: High clearance vehicle needed to reach trailhead via forest road, otherwise add ~1 mile along road. This route is shorter and less traveled than the Devils Slide Trail. Good for winter hiking since much less snow persists on the south face.
